comments.body:
This patch is same as: 
{code}
git mv hadoop-yarn-services-api hadoop-yarn-services
{code}

And modify pom.xml to match.

Created patch 2 as follows
# {{git mv hadoop-yarn-services-api hadoop-yarn-services/.}}
# Removed {{hadoop-yarn-services-api}} from the child modules of {{hadoop-yarn-applications}}
# Added {{hadoop-yarn-services-api}} as a child module of {{hadoop-yarn-services}}
# Changed the parent in {{hadoop-yarn-services-api}} to {{hadoop-yarn-services}}
# Updated the path of services-api in hadoop-yarn-dist.xml

[~gsaha] All the unit tests for Service api and service core pass on my machine.

Jenkins failed to verify the patch but I was able to run the below command successfully for the hadoop project.
{code}
mvn clean install -Pdist -Dtar -Dmaven.javadoc.skip=true -DskipShade -Danimal.sniffer.skip=true 
{code}
I'll check if something is missed.

